content:
Process Builder Is Retiring for Marketing Cloud Connect

To support the migration to Flow, Process Builder processes used by Marketing Cloud Connect are being automatically migrated to record-triggered flows. The migration occurs automatically when a journey that uses a Salesforce activity to access the object is stopped or published.

When:
- If you've enabled the View All permission, the retirement starts after Spring '24 through April 2024.
- After Process Builder is retired, the migration occurs when journeys are stopped or published.

If you haven't enabled the View All permission, the migration starts after Summer '24. Use the new Enable System Mode Flow Activation permission. Your Salesforce org and Marketing Cloud Engagement API versions must be V60.

Marketing Cloud Engagement updates to V60 on August 15, 2024 or after. After proper permissions are set, the migration occurs when journeys are stopped or published.

How: To move to record-triggered flows, enable the View All or Enable System Mode Flow Activation permission for the integration user in your account. The migration occurs when journeys that use a Salesforce activity to access the object are stopped or published.
title: Process Builder Retirement for Marketing Cloud Connect
